Preservatives may reduce the risk of infection, but do not protect 100%.
The reason is that pathogens of sexually transmitted diseases may also be transmitted through lubricating infection or close body contact.
Experts therefore recommend that any person who often changes sexual partners regularly pass examinations.
Most ISTs quickly detected can be cured and late sequelae can be avoided.
