He adds that the theme is complex, "because we ask them to have a defined criterion on what should or should not be disclosed, published or said at an age when they do not have the maturity necessary to do so."
"We also ask them to be selective when what matters most is to be popular, to have thousands of friends without thinking about the consequences," she adds.
